Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey... Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.78,0:01:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.01,0:02:06.98,EP Title BG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2000,0)\p1\blur1}m 0 0 l 950 0 950 100 0 100
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.01,0:02:06.98,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1100,0)\be1}One-Eyed Fish
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.70,0:02:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You've the ability to see mushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.62,0:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The type of mushi that give off light \Ndon't have much influential power.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.33,0:02:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it me you're afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Drink this. It'll help with your injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.86,0:02:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.48,0:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I need you to hurry and get well and leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.83,0:02:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to stay long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.37,0:03:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.17,0:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.85,0:03:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if we took the wrong road.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.25,0:03:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.37,0:03:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What, Yoki, are you seeing those weird things again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.10,0:03:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.70,0:04:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You've to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.41,0:05:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can move my foot a lot better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.65,0:05:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what kind of fish they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.21,0:05:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They're pure white with green eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.50,0:06:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all missing an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.31,0:06:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the mushi living in the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't come near here at night or at daybreak.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.69,0:06:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhm... those are not... illusions, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They're neither beings like us, nor illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But they do affect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.02,0:06:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they totally different from us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.38,0:06:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They're of a different existence\Nbut they're not disconnected from us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a different form of what we consider "life".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.77,0:06:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.85,0:06:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can walk now without a cane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.84,0:07:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoki, isn't your foot better by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.15,0:07:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You've a home to go back to, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.27,0:07:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't... have a place to go home to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.21,0:07:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I tagged along with my mom,\N who was a traveling peddler.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And... my foot... it still hurts when I walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.13,0:07:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, I've been wondering all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.50,0:07:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of mushi live in the pond? Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.30,0:07:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... well, the best way I can\N describe them is "darkness".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.24,0:07:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.20,0:07:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. There are two types of darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.16,0:07:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1633)}One is inside a shed, a moonless night,\Nor when you close your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.96,0:08:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the darkness that happens \Nwhen the sun or light is obscured.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The other darkness is "perpetual darkness".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.36,0:08:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,During the day, they lie motionless \Nin dark places like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.71,0:08:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but at night, they come out of \Nthe pond to eat smaller mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did the eye and hair color \Nchange for you and the fish in the pond?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.58,0:08:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At dawn, sometimes the pond sparkles silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.86,0:08:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably decomposing the mushi it ate into light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.97,0:08:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that if you're constantly\Nexposed to that, you become like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.87,0:08:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, won't you lose your other eye if you stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.46,0:08:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw the fish in the pond, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.77,0:08:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oddly, there are no fish with both eyes gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.36,0:08:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably the way it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.01,0:08:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now, the sun will soon set. We'd better go in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What are those mushi called?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi with the characteristics of \Ndarkness are called {\i1}Tokoyami...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:09:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The mushi that give off light seem to be a different mushi that live in {\i1}Tokoyami,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.74,0:09:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't know if those mushi have a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.39,0:09:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I call them "Ginko".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.37,0:09:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.59,0:09:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.78,0:09:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can try biting into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.61,0:09:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't swallow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.05,0:09:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.13,0:09:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ick, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.75,0:09:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.65,0:09:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your stomach will even toughen up from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.82,0:09:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.37,0:09:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! They're balled up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.02,0:09:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You broke them up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.51,0:09:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll ball right back up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.76,0:09:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I walk through the mountains,\Nit's a common occurrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.47,0:09:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, can I do that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.29,0:10:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't something you do just for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.56,0:10:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.23,0:10:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.19,0:10:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nui!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.33,0:10:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's turn on the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.08,0:10:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't aware since I can see in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it because of the {\i1}Ginko?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.49,0:10:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably. But it's a convenient ability to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.44,0:10:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Yoki, when you walk alone\Nthrough the mountains at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.21,0:10:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you may suddenly become unable to see the moon that was shining on the road
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.91,0:10:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the stars disappear so you become disoriented.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:11:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's a common occurrence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.21,0:11:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if it seems as though you're starting \Nto forget your name and past,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.65,0:11:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,, it means the {\i1}Tokoyami{\i0} is getting near.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's said that you can escape if you can \Nsomehow remember something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.69,0:11:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if I just can't remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.19,0:11:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.38,0:11:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They say to come up with a name for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.18,0:11:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.81,0:11:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But they say you won't be able to remember anything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,from the time you'd the previous name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.27,0:11:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.97,0:11:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I ask why you live here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.45,0:11:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.37,0:11:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Past these mountains lies my hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.18,0:11:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it's isolated, it's a beautiful village.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.85,0:11:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I've the tendency to attract mushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.73,0:12:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm unable to live in one place,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.97,0:12:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,so I became a mushi-shi who traveled \Naround the villages, driving mushi away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.09,0:12:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I frequently returned to my village.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.62,0:12:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To meet my parents and friends, \Nbut above all my husband and child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.44,0:12:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,However... one day, I was told that many villagers,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.31,0:12:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,including my husband and child, father and friends, went into the mountains, never to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.72,0:12:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After searching around in the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.19,0:12:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that {\i1}Tokoyami{\i0} lived in this pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.38,0:12:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd heard from other mushi-shi
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.31,0:12:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens and what to do \Nwhen captured by the {\i1}Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.59,0:12:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I continue to live here,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.64,0:12:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with the hope that the villagers\Nare still wandering around somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.12,0:13:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been six years maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.72,0:13:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By yourself for that long...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.18,0:13:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if the others have \Nthe same appearance as you do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure... they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.53,0:13:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you look for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.39,0:13:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.57,0:13:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So let me just stay...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.54,0:13:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not? Why can't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.92,0:13:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I want to do this alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.44,0:13:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.01,0:13:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make that your excuse to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say any more, I'll have you leave right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Nui is hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.50,0:14:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason why she doesn't want me to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.97,0:14:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on out, {\i1}Tokoyami, Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Its good eye is being consumed and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.33,0:14:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.84,0:14:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.06,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you it wasn't good to be exposed to that light...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.15,0:15:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Nui... The reason why all the fish \Nonly have one eye is because
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.36,0:15:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,they disappear when both eyes are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.71,0:15:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.41,0:15:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that they disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The light emitted by {\i1}Ginko{\i0}\Nturns living things into {\i1}Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.63,0:15:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same thing as disappearing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.30,0:15:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you knew that, why didn't you do anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.94,0:15:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a mushi-shi, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.73,0:15:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you allow such a terrifying mushi to live?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.00,0:15:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not let fear and anger cloud your vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.25,0:15:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all just being as they're.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.83,0:15:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the ones with wisdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.08,0:15:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so we should avoid those things that we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.91,0:15:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi-shi are people who've been seeking how to do that since long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.46,0:15:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I, too, have been taking notes on {\i1}Ginko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.00,0:15:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And, by the time I finally realized the fate of the fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.63,0:16:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd already been exposed to too much light as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I took the one-eyed fish out of the pond
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.15,0:16:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried repeatedly to protect them from the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,once the fish started turning white,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.41,0:16:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,although there was a small delay,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,they eventually lost both eyes \Nand turned into {\i1}Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.89,0:16:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No... then you're saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I refused to believe that \Nmy husband and child became {\i1}Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.73,0:16:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I stayed alive by avoiding exposure to \Nthe light and searched for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.16,0:16:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But, after all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I eventually came to realize \Nthat all the answers were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.82,0:16:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoki, if you understand what I'm saying, leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:16:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I'm sure something can be done. \NYou should leave, too, Nui!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm beyond help, and I thought \NI really didn't care anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.51,0:17:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but it just makes things harder if you stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.67,0:17:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, leave already.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.93,0:17:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you can live on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.66,0:17:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're better off not having a beloved home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.62,0:17:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No! My home is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.77,0:17:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's where I've lived the longest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.69,0:17:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No. This place is where the {\i1}Tokoyami{\i0} and I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.54,0:17:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a place for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.98,0:18:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.59,0:18:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The pond...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.25,0:18:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Nui !
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go! Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.41,0:18:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nui?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.09,0:18:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.35,0:18:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go! Nui!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.71,0:18:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:18:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nui? It's you, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.85,0:19:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.35,0:19:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ginko{\i0} will awaken soon. \NGet as far away as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.77,0:19:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now... hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.36,0:19:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hand... I don't feel anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neither cold nor warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hand is still warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.03,0:19:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And not just your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.57,0:19:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I no longer have eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.77,0:19:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you look at me, it's warm like sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.05,0:19:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,After living near that dim pond,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.77,0:19:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't know how nostalgic it made me feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.48,0:19:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Yoki. From here on, walk with one eye closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.05,0:19:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Give one eye to {\i1}Ginko
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.56,0:19:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to get away from the {\i1}Tokoyami.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.32,0:19:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But close the other eye tightly, \Nso that you'll see the sunlight again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.73,0:20:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! {\i1}Ginko{\i0} is waking up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.95,0:20:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.70,0:20:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So that's Ginko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.69,0:20:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}An eye-less fish... at the bottom of perpetual darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.08,0:20:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Do not let fear and anger cloud your vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.29,0:20:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're all just being as they're.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.74,0:20:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I smell dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.03,0:21:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the moon again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.84,0:21:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.29,0:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.77,0:21:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My name...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.17,0:21:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In times like this, what was I supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.29,0:21:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.33,0:21:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...my right eye was staring at the sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.55,0:21:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you? I've never seen you \Naround in these parts before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.65,0:21:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,H-hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.37,0:21:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hey, I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.78,0:21:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Are you well enough to be up? Don't overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.53,0:21:54.23,Alt,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:21:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}So were you able to remember anything \Nelse besides your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.59,0:22:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.59,0:22:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. If you like, you can live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.03,0:22:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's pay a visit \Nto the village head tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.19,0:22:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The only thing was...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.56,0:22:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The hole of my left eye, even in the sunlight, was black as if it was seeped in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.21,0:22:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And it attracted weird things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.35,0:22:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If it continues to do that, misfortune is sure to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.02,0:22:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1933)\i1}That's the feeling I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.09,0:22:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Ginko! Dinner time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.61,0:22:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.34,0:22:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did he go?
